The paper deals with a security and privacy issue related to computer screens, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves the use of audio signals to detect screen content, which could be categorized under sound and music computing (cs.SD). Additionally, the paper discusses the implications of this attack on human-computer interaction (cs.HC), multimedia (cs.MM), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
